### Feature Proposal

Allow `parser.javascript.importMeta` to accept an object:

```js
module.exports = {
  module: {
    parser: {
      javascript: {
        importMeta: {
          url: false,
          env: true,
          webpack: true
        }
      }
    }
  }
};
```

Existing `importMetaContext` is preserved for compatibility. `importMeta.webpackContext` has a higher priority than `importMetaContext`.


```ts
declare interface ImportMetaParserOptions {
	/**
	 * Enable/disable evaluating import.meta.dirname.
	 */
	dirname?: boolean;

	/**
	 * Enable/disable evaluating import.meta.env.
	 */
	env?: boolean;

	/**
	 * Enable/disable evaluating import.meta.filename.
	 */
	filename?: boolean;

	/**
	 * Enable/disable evaluating import.meta.main.
	 */
	main?: boolean;

	/**
	 * Enable/disable evaluating import.meta.url.
	 */
	url?: boolean;

	/**
	 * Enable/disable evaluating import.meta.webpack.
	 */
	webpack?: boolean;

	/**
	 * Enable/disable evaluating import.meta.webpackContext.
	 */
	webpackContext?: boolean;

	/**
	 * Enable/disable evaluating custom key.
	 */
	[key: string]?: boolean;
}
```

### Feature Use Case

`parser.javascript.importMeta` currently supports broad modes such as enabling webpack handling, disabling it, or preserving unknown properties. This makes it difficult to opt out of webpack processing for only one known `import.meta` field while keeping the rest of the existing behavior.

For example, a user may want webpack to keep handling `import.meta.env` and `import.meta.webpack`, but preserve native/runtime behavior for `import.meta.url`.

When a known field is set to false, webpack should preserve that import.meta.* access for runtime evaluation instead of replacing or specially handling it.
Unknown fields should continue to be preserved when using the object form.


### Additional Context

https://github.com/web-infra-dev/rspack/pull/12266

> This PR fixes an issue where import.meta.url was unconditionally replaced by the local file path during the build, causing file:/// URLs to appear in web builds.
